dpul.title: Batch Ingested Princeton-Only MVW Scanned Resources are syncing to DPUL as extracted individual volumes

comments.body:
We found this is true, and it's the same problem as before. Example: https://figgy.princeton.edu/catalog/6b4b1f2b-3485-40e8-a956-3050c927b35c. Both of the volumes have a collection and should not. We thought we made this impossible to happen again here: https://github.com/pulibrary/figgy/pull/5695 

We think maybe bulk ingest is adding collections to volumes (bulk ingesting pdfs?)

## Success Criteria

1. The volumes have no collections associated.
2. Bulk ingest does not add collections to volumes.
   * If this isn't the problem, then find out (with @tventimi probably) how these got ingested so we can identify how they got collections attached to them.

comments.body: Blocking for more info about what should be happening here. @regineheberlein will follow up

We've consulted with Willow and decided that engineering materials should not be requestable from the finding aid, since they are in the open stacks. 

The desired behavior for engineering records (all of which have location `st`) is to not have the request button. Is that possible?

If it would help / be easier we could also remove the container locations from all ENG records in ArchivesSpace.
